Description:
Vast factory conversion, outstanding potential
The former Gregory Steel Products factory, set on a huge block (465 sq.m approx) moments from Smith Street's cafe scene, is Collingwood's premier investment opportunity. Zoned Commercial 1, this grand red brick property with remnant industrial detail has brilliant scope for further development (STCA). Including 4-car garaging, a multi-room apartment/office suite with private entry and huge storeroom, this astounding building incorporates an impressively spacious residence with high ceilings, flanked by wide courtyards accessed from all principal rooms. It comprises 4 double bedrooms, expansive living and dining zones, well-equipped kitchen, 2 superbly fitted bathrooms plus large laundry, and features polished timber floors, ample storage, heating and cooling.
Insights: 10 Perry Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 1 other 5 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Ubercool cafe precinct space & style
Just metres from Smith Street's renowned cafes, restaurants and bars, this stylish and spacious residence at the rear of a boutique development offers uniquely secluded living with the special attraction of private lift access from 2 levels to a secure LU garage. A versatile floor plan incorporates 3 well-separated double BRs (ensuite and fitted dressing room to main), large reception area/office, vast light-filled living and dining area open to custom kitchen with stone benchtops and imported appliances, luxurious bathroom (bath and shower) and laundry. Including balconies and terraces, this exclusive CBD residence features storage, video intercom security and split-system air conditioning. Nelson Alexander Pty. Ltd.

Description:
Shopfront and dwelling: space and style!
Formerly a corner butcher shop and adjoining house, this historic property is now an exceptionally spacious 3/4BR family residence, combining period character with light-filled style. Close to great cafes and bars, Gold St Primary, Queens Parade and transport, it offers a versatile floor plan comprising 3 double bedrooms (BIRs), spacious living and dining rooms, sitting room/4th BR, upper level family room opening to deck with northerly views, well-equipped kitchen (Bosch appliances) and 2 stylish bathrooms, one with concealed laundry. Including a sunny courtyard with OSP from Charlotte St, this captivating home features polished concrete floors, OFPs and other Victorian detail, split-system air conditioning and storage.

Description:
Immaculate Edwardian, excellent position
In a quiet local traffic-only street close to Smith St, transport, local bars and cafes, this appealing tuck-pointed period home offers comfortable, light-filled living with wonderful scope for future enhancement. Featuring Baltic floors, Art Nouveau fretwork detail and open fireplaces, it has a classic floor plan comprising 2 double bedrooms, spacious living room adjoining light court, sunny dining zone open to modernised kitchen with granite benchtops and stainless steel stove, updated white-tiled bathroom and concealed laundry. Opening to the rear is a north-easterly ROW access courtyard, ready for summer al fresco living. A perfect first home or prime investment!

Description:
'Inner city' has a name - 'Islington'
The location of this huge one bedroom apartment sums up precisely what we mean when we say 'inner city'. Its proximity to the CBD, North Richmond station, the parkland of East Melbourne and the vibrancy of Victoria Street ensures a sensational lifestyle matches its established record of delivering investment returns. Living and dining areas of exceptional size and style for a one bedroom format are complemented by a generous balcony and an open plan kitchen featuring ample integrated storage. In its own zone, the inviting double bedroom with built-in robes is served in style by a separate central bathroom. Reverse cycle heating/cooling provides constant comfort throughout these generous third floor spaces that are further enhanced by complete security and allocated car parking. An engaging, enticing example of city edge excellence.

Description:
Outstanding value in 'Prime' pocket
Be at home in contemporary spaces of the highest calibre created by Map Architecture & Design and designers Eades & Bergman from the iconic basis of the Islington Silos. This spacious apartment illustrates the residential refinement has been introduced to an inner city setting of character and convenience close to Victoria Parade trams and trains from North Richmond station. A generous living/dining domain that gives low-maintenance ease an elegant edge is complemented by an open plan kitchen featuring gleaming stone benches, impressive appliances and integrated storage while the consummate comfort of two double bedrooms is enhanced by a beautifully appointed central bathroom. A spacious balcony issues an invitation to enjoy an outdoor and indoor lifestyle with an industrial edge. Secure garaging completes an outstanding inner city opportunity.

Description:
Boutique luxury in Little Ox
Designer style and an abundance of northerly light highlight the appeal of this second-floor Little Ox apartment situated in a prime Fitzroy-edge location moments from the buzz of Smith Street and walking distance to everything that counts. First-class interior comprises main bedroom (with robes) and separate study/2nd bedroom, classy bathroom, open lounge/meals area leading out to a full-width undercover decked balcony. Add to this a stone-top kitchen with soft-close drawers, ample cupboard space, Ilve cooking appliances and dishwasher, split-system heating and cooling, quality carpets and engineered oak floors, European laundry, plus video intercom, lift access to secure entry foyer and large storage cage. Close to trams and buses, shops and supermarkets, cafe culture and renowned restaurants. Inner-city perfection!

Private & luxurious, this spacious 3 bedroom apartment split over 3 levels with architecture inspired by Piet Mondrian and a gallery-like entrance is a unique and rare opportunity not to be missed. With a private on-street entrance, twin balconies with 270 degree views (sunrise over Mt Dandenong to sunset over Smith Street just 150m away), this highly desirable residence features clean, modern aesthetics throughout. The home features polished concrete floors on level 1, dark timber floors across levels 2 & 3, floor to ceiling built-in storage in all bedrooms, a master bedroom with en-suite, Miele kitchen appliances, Heating & A/C in every room, and secure off street storage with parking for 2 (via stacker). Nestled right in the heart of the vibrant Smith St district, this is a prime location for families, young couples or investors looking for high yield rental, extremely close to some of best casual & fine dining in Melbourne (Proud Mary, Saint Crispin, Alimentari, Easy Tiger), and provides easy walking distance to the Yarra, the CBD, and 4 of the best parks & gardens in Melbourne (Edinburgh Gardens, Fitzroy Gardens, Carlton Gardens, Studley Park).
Insights: 9 Little Wellington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Melbourne meets Manhattan
In the heart of Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct, this top-floor warehouse loft invokes a New York state of mind with its vast open spaces, bold industrial remnants and spectacular feature ceilings. Designer interior highlights 2 bedrooms (huge mezzanine-style master and adjoining study/home office), stylish main bathroom and additional powder room, vast open-plan living/dining area complemented by towering ceilings with original timberwork and clerestory windows for an abundance of natural light. Add to this a sleek kitchen with walk-in pantry and Bosch dishwasher, polished floorboards, Euro laundry, plus secure foyer and undercover parking space. Close to everything that counts, Smith Street cafes and restaurants, shops and supermarkets, city-bound trams are all within easy reach.

Description:
Ave Maria, thank the heavens!
Providing all the certainty of a secure investment, this classical Victorian brick terrace ("Ave Maria," circa 1890s) offers an accessible launching pad into a tightly held neighbourhood. Enter via a verandah showcasing elegant wrought-iron work and discover an inviting hallway and 2 large bedrooms. The home then spectacularly opens up to reveal a light-filled living and dining room adjoining a functional kitchen. Step outside to a north-facing courtyard with laneway access and plenty of room for off-street parking. ?Offering instantly enjoyable living with further potential to update and add value, stroll to Smith and Gertrude Streets, Victoria Park Station and Abbotsford Convent with its enticing mix of restaurants and parkland. This is classic inner-city living with all the rewards!
* 2 large bedrooms
* Spacious living and dining room
* Functional kitchen
* Bathroom with bath and laundry capabilities
* Roomy courtyard with laneway access and capacity for off-street parking
* Stylish palm trees providing shade to north-facing courtyard
* Storage room running alongside house
* High ceilings and charming period flourishes throughout
* Gas heating
* Moments from Smith Street restaurants, Victoria Park Station, Eastern Freeway, parkland
Insights: 130 Keele Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.
